    pub const WAND: (&str, &str) = ("Wand", "A wand contains a single spell which you can cast once per day. After the spell is cast from the wand for the day, you can attempt to cast it one more time � overcharging the wand at the risk of destroying it. (action: Cast the Spell | Cast a Spell) again, then roll a DC 10 flat check. On a success, the wand is broken. On a failure, the wand is destroyed. If anyone tries to overcharge a wand when it�s already been overcharged that day, the wand is automatically destroyed (even if it had been repaired) and no spell is cast. A wand has all the traits of the spell it contains.");
